// ---- Extend BGM slots from 16 to 25 ----
// 1. getVersusBgmNum: change MOV W8, #16 -> MOV W8, #25 (default versus path)
000E86B8 28038052

// 2. Replace choiceBgm entirely with our hook that uses static storage sized for 25 BGMs.
//    This fixes the crash: the original function has both the free-node pool and the
//    PtrArray buffer hardcoded to 16 entries on the stack. With 25 BGMs requested,
//    bgmfuncthign exhausts the pool at node 17 (NULL deref) AND overflows the buffer.
//    NOTE: The setBuffer capacity patch (376A28) is intentionally omitted here —
//    choiceBgmHook never calls setBuffer; it manages its own static struct.
// 	  special thanks to mr claude for this shit i was going to end it all
00376950 B choiceBgmHook

